snippet.textDisplay:
Hi folks back again only this time it's about my team the Gers so here's my take on the game :- 1st the usually saviour comes to our rescue in timely fashion with a well assisted goal " EĽ BUFFÀLO " 28 All Comps I think, not bad for 1 game until the end of the 1st half to the season. The only thing I have to add about the Glasgow Rangers is that the players have to be a whole lot more clinical with their end product /finishing off. Also why is it that once we have a team on the ropes we're struggling to get a much larger goal difference in these games where after the 3rd or 4th goal that we don't go and Terry Butcher the opposition and get 3-4 more goals
Take that extra mo to think and watch the team flourish into the Rangers Hall of Fame like all the greats who went on to what they thought wete better things. Some made it others didn't, but the best left after they'd helped the Gers to success after success it's a thing called " PRIDE " you have it or you don't simple. Goal difference counts esp.. at the end of the season tied on points and lose league by a goal =Gutted Fans. Now reverse the situation to winning by a goal and you will have undying adulation from Adults to the kids best Christmas and New year's present you Can give the Fans. Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year Too you All teams, clubs faiths and denominations.
Mr. D. Kennedy. All the best folks.
Was the only two I'd seen clips of.
